InternLink Platform
1. Chosen Development Model
Development Model: Agile

Justification:

Agile is chosen for InternLink because the platform requires frequent updates, UI changes, and backend refinements as stakeholders (students, companies, university) give feedback.
Agile allows:

- Iterative development through sprints
- Continuous improvement
- Flexibility for new requirements
- Clear task division among team members

2. User Requirements

a. Stakeholders (WHO is involved)
Stakeholder	Role in InternLink	Interest
- Students (End-Users):	Browse, filter, and apply for opportunities. Want a simple portal to find verified internships & events
- Companies:	Post, edit, delete their opportunities. Want easy advertisement and student access
- Epoka University Staff:	Verify, monitor, and support posted opportunities. Ensure quality, legitimacy, and relevance
- Administrators:	Manage system, users, and approvals. Maintain data accuracy and platform integrity
- Development Team (InternLink Team):	Build the platform. Need clear requirements, structured workflow

b. User Stories
Students
As a student, I want to browse and filter opportunities so that I can quickly find relevant internships.
As a student, I want to view detailed opportunity information so that I understand requirements before applying.
As a student, I want to apply through the platform so that I can submit applications easily and on time.
As a student, I want to save/bookmark opportunities so that I can review them later.
As a student, I want to receive notifications about new opportunities so that I do not miss deadlines.

Companies

As a company, I want to post new opportunities so that students can discover them.
As a company, I want to edit or delete my listings so that information remains accurate.
As a company, I want to view student applications so that I can evaluate candidates.
As a company, I want to download applicant documents so that I can review them offline.
As a company, I want to close opportunities after the deadline so that no further applications are accepted.

University Staff

As university staff, I want to verify opportunities so that only legitimate ones are published.

Administrator
As an admin, I want to manage users so that the system remains organized and secure.
As an admin, I want to approve or reject listings so that platform integrity is maintained.

3. Functional Requirements

3.1 User Management

FR1 – User Registration
The system shall allow users to register by providing required fields (name, email, password, role) and ensure the email is unique.

FR2 – User Login
The system shall authenticate users using email and password and allow access only if credentials are valid.

FR3 – Role-Based Access Control
The system shall restrict system features based on user roles.

FR4 – Profile Management
Users shall be able to view and update their profile information.

FR5 – Password Recovery
The system shall allow users to reset their password via email verification.

3.2 Student Features

FR6 – View Opportunities
The system shall display approved opportunities sorted by relevance or deadline.

FR7 – Search Opportunities
The system shall return opportunities based on keyword matches.

FR8 – Filter Opportunities
The system shall allow filtering by category, location, type, and deadline.

FR9 – View Opportunity Details
The system shall display full details including requirements and company information.

FR10 – Apply to Opportunities
The system shall allow students to submit applications linked to an opportunity.

FR11 – Application Tracking
The system shall display application status updates.

3.3 Company Features

FR12 – Post Opportunity
Companies shall submit opportunities with required details.

FR13 – Edit Opportunity
Companies shall update their own listings.

FR14 – Delete Opportunity
Companies shall remove their listings from the system.

FR15 – View Verification Status
Companies shall see the approval status of their listings.

FR16 – Manage Company Profile
Companies shall update their profile details.

3.4 University Staff Features

FR17 – Review Opportunities
Staff shall view all pending opportunities.

FR18 – Approve/Reject Opportunities
Staff shall assign approval status to listings.

3.5 Admin Features

FR19 – Manage Users
Admin shall view and filter all users.

FR20 – Enable/Disable Accounts
Admin shall control user account access.

FR21 – Moderate Opportunities
Admin shall edit, approve, reject, or delete any listing.

FR22 – Monitor System Activity
Admin shall view system statistics via dashboard.

FR23 – Assign Roles
Admin shall update user roles.

3.6 System Requirements

FR24 – Dashboard Display
The system shall provide role-specific dashboards.

FR25 – Pagination
The system shall limit results per page.

FR26 – Data Storage
The system shall securely store all platform data.

FR27 – API Communication
The system shall use REST APIs for all operations.

FR28 – Security Enforcement
The system shall enforce authentication and validation on all actions.

b. Acceptance Criteria (4-5 REQUIREMENTS TO DO THE ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA)

- Login & Registration (All users)

User enters valid credentials → system authenticates against the database and grants access
User enters invalid credentials → error message is displayed
After login, user is redirected to their role-specific dashboard

Student Features:

- Browse Opportunities

Student views a list of internship opportunities in paginated format
Filters (location, type, deadline) return relevant results
Filtered results update without page reload

- Apply to Opportunity (External Link)

Student clicks “Apply” → system redirects to the company’s external application link
External link opens correctly in a new tab
System does not store application data

- Save Opportunity

Student can save/bookmark an opportunity
Saved opportunities appear in the student’s dashboard
Student can remove saved opportunities at any time

Company Features:

- Post Opportunity

Company submits a new opportunity including an external application link
Opportunity is saved in the database
Status is set to “Pending Verification”

- Edit/Delete Opportunity

Company updates or deletes a listing → changes are saved successfully
Updates are reflected across all dashboards

University Staff Features:

- Verify Opportunities

Staff can view all pending opportunity submissions
Staff can approve or reject a listing
Status changes are visible to company and admin users

Admin Features:

- Manage System

Admin can view all registered users
Admin can enable or disable user accounts
Admin can approve, reject, or edit any opportunity

4. Non-Functional Requirements

a. Description

Performance: Pages should load quickly, even with many listings.
Usability: Dashboards must be clean, intuitive, and consistent.
Reliability: System should provide stable uptime.
Security: Passwords encrypted; role-based access enforced.
Scalability: System must support increasing users as Epoka expands opportunities.

b. Acceptance Criteria

Speed

Student dashboard (opportunity listings) loads in under 2 seconds
Filtering internships by field, location, or company updates in under 1 second
Application submissions are processed instantly without noticeable delay

Security

User passwords are securely hashed using bcrypt
JWT authentication is used to manage user sessions
Users can only access features based on their role (student, company, university staff, admin)
Unauthorized users cannot view or modify applications or postings

Usability

Students can easily browse and apply for internships without guidance
Companies can create and manage opportunities in a few simple steps
University staff can quickly approve or reject postings
Interface remains consistent across all dashboards

Reliability

Platform maintains over 99% uptime
Applications and opportunity data are saved reliably without loss
System handles multiple users applying and posting simultaneously without errors

5. Application Specifications

a. Architecture

InternLink uses a three-tier architecture: frontend, backend, and database.
The frontend (React) provides dashboards for different users and communicates with the backend via APIs.
The backend (Node.js/Express or Flask) handles logic and data processing.
The database (MySQL/PostgreSQL) stores all system data.

b. Database Model

The system uses a relational database.
Main tables include Users, Opportunities, Applications, and Verification, which are connected through relationships to keep data organized and consistent.

c. Technologies Used

Frontend: React, HTML, CSS, JavaScript
Backend: Node.js/Express
Database: MySQL or PostgreSQL
Authentication: JWT and bcrypt
Version control: GitHub

d. User Interface Design

The platform provides simple dashboards for each user role.
Students can browse and apply for opportunities, companies manage listings, staff verify posts, and admins oversee the system.

e. Security Measures

Passwords are encrypted, and user sessions are secured with tokens.
Access is controlled by user roles, inputs are validated, and the system is protected against common security threats.
